http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Proposed-SAR-structure/article14018956.ece

The Governor will function as the administrator of the proposed Sabarimala SAR, the BJP memorandum says.A governing board may be formed with the participation of the Centre, the State governments of Kerala, Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, and Andhra Pradesh, and the Travancore Devaswom Board. A proper executive system can also be set up for better governance. SAR can have departments to look after essential, emergency, and municipal functions. The heads of these departments should be permanently employed by the governing board and be accountable to the administrator.Democratic participation may be ensured through the presence of the local MP and MLA on the governing board. The District Collector may also join the board for coordinating with the local administration.Sabari Rail CorporationThe BJP also called for setting up a separate Sabari Rail Corporation on the lines of the Konkan Railway Corporation. It said the Centre should have 51 per cent stake in the proposed corporation, while Kerala, Tamil Nadu, Karnataka, Telangana, and Andhra Pradesh should have the remaining stake